gases for all the time it's

00:32:14.850 --> 00:32:19.440
living and breathing,
plus in general,

00:32:19.440 --> 00:32:21.450
feeding grain to
cattle, in particular,

00:32:21.450 --> 00:32:24.930
is hugely inefficient depending
on how you measure it.

00:32:24.930 --> 00:32:26.910
Roughly a 20 to 1
conversion of what

00:32:26.910 --> 00:32:33.180
we feed cattle to convert it
to editable food for humans.

00:32:33.180 --> 00:32:34.290
Massively inefficient.

00:32:34.290 --> 00:32:36.540
And of course the production
of all that grain and soy

00:32:36.540 --> 00:32:38.040
that we feed to
them has the kind

00:32:38.040 --> 00:32:42.580
of environmental footprints
that Gina is talking about.

00:32:42.580 --> 00:32:47.460
So in the end, we came up
with some numbers per se

00:32:47.460 --> 00:32:52.020
red meat which might be low by
