00:32:57.930 --> 00:33:00.120
That amounts to about
one hamburger per week,

00:33:00.120 --> 00:33:04.050
or a big steak once a month.

00:33:04.050 --> 00:33:05.760
And some people would
think that's small,

00:33:05.760 --> 00:33:08.500
but actually the
amount of poultry

00:33:08.500 --> 00:33:12.220
plus red meat that we suggest
in terms of target numbers

00:33:12.220 --> 00:33:14.410
is a bit more than
what was consumed

00:33:14.410 --> 00:33:18.580
in the traditional Mediterranean
diet when it was really

00:33:18.580 --> 00:33:20.740
traditional, before the
industrialization of it

00:33:20.740 --> 00:33:22.960
back in the 1950s and 1960s.

00:33:22.960 --> 00:33:26.500
And at that time people had
the longest life expectancy

00:33:26.500 --> 00:33:29.800
in the world, those men
consuming the Mediterranean

00:33:29.800 --> 00:33:31.840
diet at that time.

00:33:31.840 --> 00:33:35.510
Now this is partly
how we think of food,

00:33:35.510 --> 00:33:38.990
red meat in the Mediterranean
diet is something special.

00:33:38.990 --> 00:33:40.900
We might have small
amounts in a mixed dish,

00:33:40.900 --> 00:33:45.150
or as a celebratory
event, and in fact

00:33:45.150 --> 00:33:47.380
it's really about
we have to shift

00:33:47.380 --> 00:33:51.700
our thinking into something
like I consider lobster, which

00:33:51.700 --> 00:33:54.700
hopefully the Maine
people will appreciate,

00:33:54.700 --> 00:33:58.750
that I really like it, but it's
not something I eat every day.

00:33:58.750 --> 00:34:00.680
It's a special event.

00:34:00.680 --> 00:34:02.920
And that's sort of
how we, I think,

00:34:02.920 --> 00:34:05.920
need to shift toward thinking
about some of the foods

00:34:05.920 --> 00:34:08.090
we have in our diet.

00:34:08.090 --> 00:34:11.260
We have, fortunately,
lots of traditional diets

00:34:11.260 --> 00:34:15.730
from around the world that
are healthy and sustainable,

00:34:15.730 --> 00:34:19.870
and the best studied one
is the Mediterranean diet.

00:34:19.870 --> 00:34:24.429
And we've learned a lot using
that as an example in terms

00:34:24.429 --> 00:34:28.389
of analysis, and one of the
good things about all of this

00:34:28.389 --> 00:34:31.580
is that we have a
double win situation.

00:34:31.580 --> 00:34:34.420
We can improve our
health and improve

00:34:34.420 --> 00:34:36.790
the environmental
impact, in fact,

00:34:36.790 --> 00:34:39.280
to make it sustainable
in the long run

00:34:39.280 --> 00:34:42.500
by adopting this, what
some people would call it

00:34:42.500 --> 00:34:43.510
a flexitarian diet.

00:34:43.510 --> 00:34:45.340
It's not a vegetarian
diet or a vegan diet,

00:34:45.340 --> 00:34:48.520
but one that emphasizes
plant sources of protein.

00:34:48.520 --> 00:34:51.489
So better health,
better environment,

00:34:51.489 --> 00:34:54.699
and as Ana has really shown and
that chefs across the country

00:34:54.699 --> 00:34:57.250
have really shown to,
it can be a triple win,

00:34:57.250 --> 00:35:01.330
with being marvelously
enjoyable and tasty.

00:35:01.330 --> 00:35:05.020
To accomplish this, we've worked
a lot with the culinary world,

00:35:05.020 --> 00:35:07.360
in particular our partners
at the Culinary Institute

00:35:07.360 --> 00:35:10.900
of America, bringing
together major food services

00:35:10.900 --> 00:35:17.830
around the country, having chefs
really demonstrate and show how

00:35:17.830 --> 00:35:19.700
to put this into practice.

00:35:19.700 --> 00:35:23.288
But as some have mentioned
m really starting at home

00:35:23.288 --> 00:35:23.830
is important.

00:35:23.830 --> 00:35:27.730
We worked right here with
Harvard Dining Service,

00:35:27.730 --> 00:35:29.560
and we've had good
partners there.

00:35:29.560 --> 00:35:31.870
We have really changed
our food service

00:35:31.870 --> 00:35:36.460
in a way that emphasizes
the kind of dietary balance

00:35:36.460 --> 00:35:37.780
that we're talking about.

00:35:37.780 --> 00:35:41.995
And actually our food service
is a destination place

00:35:41.995 --> 00:35:43.870
that people come from
around the medical area

00:35:43.870 --> 00:35:46.150
to enjoy the food
that we have here.

00:35:46.150 --> 00:35:51.100
It's not just healthy and
sustainable, it's enjoyable.

00:35:51.100 --> 00:35:54.500
Some of this has been
behind the scenes.

00:35:54.500 --> 00:35:56.560
For example, we
worked with before it

00:35:56.560 --> 00:36:00.430
