[LAUGHTER]

00:41:25.722 --> 00:41:27.180
DAVID FREEMAN:
Another thing that I

00:41:27.180 --> 00:41:28.545
want to talk about,
Gina kind of referenced

00:41:28.545 --> 00:41:30.300
this earlier about the
idea of food waste,

00:41:30.300 --> 00:41:32.668
and what are some of
the things that we

00:41:32.668 --> 00:41:33.960
might do to prevent food waste?

00:41:33.960 --> 00:41:35.730
As you said it's such
a huge contributor

00:41:35.730 --> 00:41:38.987
to greenhouse gas emissions,
and as well as economic problem.

00:41:38.987 --> 00:41:41.070
GINA MCCARTHY: Well, it's
just like anything else,

00:41:41.070 --> 00:41:43.600
waste comes at every
