what role crickets

00:46:28.280 --> 00:46:30.560
play in the world's food supply.

00:46:30.560 --> 00:46:33.530
WALTER WILLETT: Well, it
certainly is a hot topic now

00:46:33.530 --> 00:46:35.540
and we need to
learn more about it,

00:46:35.540 --> 00:46:39.410
but many cultures have used
insects as a traditional food.

00:46:39.410 --> 00:46:42.080
From the nutrient content,
it looks pretty good.

00:46:42.080 --> 00:46:44.330
The reality is, of course,
we don't have any long term

00:46:44.330 --> 00:46:47.880
studies that we'd really like
to have, but in the meantime,

00:46:47.880 --> 00:46:53.070
we think integrating some of
these into our food systems

00:46:53.070 --> 00:46:56.730
is useful way to proceed.

00:46:56.730 --> 00:47:01.310
But we should study them as
we go through this process.

00:47:01.310 --> 00:47:04.460
Insects can also have some
intermediate role, too,

00:47:04.460 --> 00:47:09.500
taking foods that are high in
cellulose that we can't digest,

00:47:09.500 --> 00:47:11.690
and converting that
food to something

00:47:11.690 --> 00:47:13.660
that chickens or fish can eat.

00:47:13.660 --> 00:47:16.850
And so there's some interesting
loops we can put into the cycle

00:47:16.850 --> 00:47:19.610
there where insects could
play an important role.

