and they go in cities,

00:50:49.220 --> 00:50:52.490
and they sign people up to be
able to use their front lawn

00:50:52.490 --> 00:50:56.960
to grow food, and the people get
to really use the food as much

00:50:56.960 --> 00:51:00.440
as they want, and they
harvest it when it's ready.

00:51:00.440 --> 00:51:03.380
And they sell the
what they harvest,

00:51:03.380 --> 00:51:06.890
and it provides a
little good economic job

00:51:06.890 --> 00:51:09.080
for a lot of young people.

00:51:09.080 --> 00:51:11.660
Only it provides
awesome opportunities

00:51:11.660 --> 00:51:13.970
for fresh food for
those families.

00:51:13.970 --> 00:51:17.420
Now you have to be careful in
the city that the soil is good,

00:51:17.420 --> 00:51:22.220
and it's clean enough to you to
not sort of sneak other things

00:51:22.220 --> 00:51:24.140
into your food as it grows.

00:51:24.140 --> 00:51:29.060
But it's just there's so much
we could do to be more creative.

00:51:29.060 --> 00:51:33.080
And to me anything you can do
to personalize these issues,

00:51:33.080 --> 00:51:37.340
make people have the
power over these things,

00:51:37.340 --> 00:51:39.440
the better not they're
going to demand

00:51:39.440 --> 00:51:44.090
that they have really
strong naturally

00:51:44.090 --> 00:51:49.450
produced products that
they'll be comfortable with.

00:51:49.450 --> 00:51:51.950
And I think it's great.

00:51:51.950 --> 00:51:55.138
Everyone can get involved
in these types of issues.

00:51:55.138 --> 00:51:56.180
DAVID FREEMAN: Thank you.

